target_text:
And is he dead, or absent ? Memories wake
Of all he was, alive, or dwelling here ;

The past we fondly cherish for his sake ;

We thought, while present, that we held him dear,
But intervening spaces only make

Him tenfold dearer than we thought him, near ;

A look, a picture, a remembered tone
Recals him as he once was all our own.

