Here paused thy swiftly flowing pen,
Never again to flow for me ;

Our glad communion ended then,

In this thy latest gift to me.

VII.

Alas ! our living love may change,

A brother’s heart may turn to stone ;
To newer objects love may range ;
Repelled, may eat its heart alone.

